    "body": "Mobile designs are [available here in Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/aS1ct66VQ6V0cio7vSqS8UoG/Chat?node-id=1244%3A9109). @lukaszfryc both the iOS and Android Action Sheet menu will be made obsolete by our own [bottom sheet component](https://www.figma.com/file/cb4p8AxLtTF3q1L6JYDnKN15/Index?node-id=5%3A220) that aims to unify the design across both platforms, I say good riddance :) But that's beside the point anyway since it's not the right fit for the reaction interface being so disconnected from the message and covering it altogether. That's why the long press menu should behave exactly like in the prototype, there are two tooltips appearing above the message: one bottom tooltip for actions like Reply, Copy ‚Äî and I'll also propose to replace the share we have now with a much more useful forwarding in a separate issue ‚Äî and another top tooltip for housing reactions. \r\n\r\nOutside the scope of this issue: including Forward inside the action menu, SNT reactions.",
